<subSubSection pageId="26" pageNumber="27" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="26.[151,1436,898,1124]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">
Newly recorded in Nova Scotia (
<figureCitation box="[604,695,1018,1044]" captionStart="FIGURE 12" captionStartId="27.[151,255,1372,1396]" captionTargetBox="[207,1400,331,1286]" captionTargetId="figure-158@27.[172,1419,313,1320]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURE 12. Distribution of Hadrobregmus notatus (Say), Oligomerus sericans (Melsheimer), Stegobium paniceum (Linnaeus), and Anobium punctatum (DeGeer) in the Maritime Provinces of Canada." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5096675" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5096675/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Fig. 12</figureCitation>
). Widely distributed in the eastern and central 
<collectingCountry box="[1275,1435,1018,1044]" name="United States of America" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">United States</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="White, R. E." box="[158,304,1058,1084]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" pagination="529 - 70" refId="ref23969" refString="White, R. E. (1982) A catalogue of the Coleoptera of America north of Mexico, Family Anobiidae. United States Department of Agriculture, Agricultural Research Service, Agricultural Handbook 529 - 70." type="book chapter" year="1982">White 1982</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Downie, N. M. &amp; Arnett, R. H., Jr." box="[319,605,1058,1084]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" refId="ref22003" refString="Downie, N. M. &amp; Arnett, R. H., Jr. (1996) The beetles of northeastern North America. Sandhill Crane Press, Gainesville, Florida. 1721 pp." type="book" year="1996">Downie &amp; Arnett 1996</bibRefCitation>
); in 
<collectingCountry box="[663,751,1058,1084]" name="Canada" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Canada</collectingCountry>
recorded from 
<collectingRegion box="[942,1032,1058,1084]" country="Canada" name="Ontario" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Ontario</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingRegion box="[1095,1184,1058,1084]" country="Canada" name="Quebec" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Québec</collectingRegion>
(
<bibRefCitation author="McNamara, J." box="[1203,1424,1058,1084]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" pagination="201 - 205" refId="ref23391" refString="McNamara, J. (1991 c) Family Anobiidae: deathwatch beetles. In Bousquet, Y. (Ed.) Checklist of Beetles of Canada and Alaska. Agriculture Canada Publication 1861 / E. Ottawa, Ontario, pp. 201 - 205." type="book chapter" year="1991">McNamara 1991c</bibRefCitation>
). Found on English walnut, chestnut, and white oak (
<bibRefCitation author="White, R. E." box="[753,897,1098,1124]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" pagination="529 - 70" refId="ref23969" refString="White, R. E. (1982) A catalogue of the Coleoptera of America north of Mexico, Family Anobiidae. United States Department of Agriculture, Agricultural Research Service, Agricultural Handbook 529 - 70." type="book chapter" year="1982">White 1982</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
